---
export const prerender = true;
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About — Privacy Terminal" description="What Privacy Terminal is, why it exists, and how it works. Full transparency about our tools, methods, and principles.">
  <div class="mb-8">
    <h1 class="text-terminal-green text-glow-green text-lg font-bold mb-2">
      <span class="text-terminal-muted">~/</span>about
    </h1>
  </div>

  <div class="space-y-8">
    <!-- What is this -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-terminal-green text-sm font-bold mb-3 pb-2 border-b border-terminal-border">
        ## What is Privacy Terminal?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
        Privacy Terminal is an open-source collection of browser-based privacy tools and
        educational guides. We help you understand your digital footprint and take practical
        steps to reduce it.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Every tool runs entirely in your browser. Your data never touches our servers.
        Every guide presents the full landscape of options without pushing a single solution.
        Every line of code is publicly auditable.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Principles -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-terminal-green text-sm font-bold mb-3 pb-2 border-b border-terminal-border">
        ## Principles
      </h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="border border-terminal-border rounded p-4">
          <h3 class="text-terminal-cyan text-xs font-bold mb-2">Privacy by Architecture</h3>
          <p class="text-terminal-muted text-xs leading-relaxed">
            We don't ask you to trust us with your data — we've built the system so we never
            see it. Tools run client-side. No server processing. No database. No logs.
            This isn't a policy choice, it's an architectural one.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-terminal-border rounded p-4">
          <h3 class="text-terminal-cyan text-xs font-bold mb-2">The Landscape Principle</h3>
          <p class="text-terminal-muted text-xs leading-relaxed">
            Every guide shows you the full spectrum of options with honest trade-offs.
            We don't tell you "use X" — we show you what exists, what each option costs
            (in money, convenience, and complexity), and let you decide what fits your
            threat model.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-terminal-border rounded p-4">
          <h3 class="text-terminal-cyan text-xs font-bold mb-2">Verify, Don't Trust</h3>
          <p class="text-terminal-muted text-xs leading-relaxed">
            Our source code is public. Our tools run in your browser where you can inspect
            them with DevTools. We cite our sources. We explain our methodology.
            If you can't verify a privacy claim, it's not worth making.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-terminal-border rounded p-4">
          <h3 class="text-terminal-cyan text-xs font-bold mb-2">Education Over Products</h3>
          <p class="text-terminal-muted text-xs leading-relaxed">
            We believe privacy tools without privacy education create a false sense of security.
            Understanding <em>why</em> something matters is more durable than knowing
            <em>which app</em> to install.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Transparency -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-terminal-green text-sm font-bold mb-3 pb-2 border-b border-terminal-border">
        ## Transparency Report
      </h2>
      <div class="terminal-window">
        <div class="terminal-titlebar">
          <div class="flex gap-2">
            <div class="terminal-dot terminal-dot-red"></div>
            <div class="terminal-dot terminal-dot-amber"></div>
            <div class="terminal-dot terminal-dot-green"></div>
          </div>
          <span class="text-terminal-muted text-xs ml-2 select-none">transparency.log</span>
        </div>
        <div class="terminal-body text-xs space-y-2">
          <div><span class="text-terminal-green">tracking_scripts:</span> <span class="text-terminal-red">none</span></div>
          <div><span class="text-terminal-green">cookies_set:</span> <span class="text-terminal-red">none</span></div>
          <div><span class="text-terminal-green">external_requests:</span> <span class="text-terminal-red">none</span></div>
          <div><span class="text-terminal-green">third_party_js:</span> <span class="text-terminal-red">none</span></div>
          <div><span class="text-terminal-green">user_accounts:</span> <span class="text-terminal-red">none</span></div>
          <div><span class="text-terminal-green">data_collected:</span> <span class="text-terminal-red">none</span></div>
          <div><span class="text-terminal-green">server_logs:</span> <span class="text-gray-400">Cloudflare standard (IP addresses not stored by us)</span></div>
          <div><span class="text-terminal-green">source_code:</span> <a href="https://github.com/vespillo-tech/privacyterminal" class="text-terminal-cyan">github.com/vespillo-tech/privacyterminal</a></div>
          <div><span class="text-terminal-green">security_contact:</span> <a href="/.well-known/security.txt" class="text-terminal-cyan">/.well-known/security.txt</a></div>
          <div><span class="text-terminal-green">hosting:</span> <span class="text-gray-400">Cloudflare Pages (static)</span></div>
          <div><span class="text-terminal-green">monetization:</span> <span class="text-gray-400">none currently — trust-first approach</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- How to verify -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-terminal-green text-sm font-bold mb-3 pb-2 border-b border-terminal-border">
        ## How to Verify Our Claims
      </h2>
      <div class="text-sm text-gray-300 space-y-3">
        <div class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-terminal-green shrink-0">1.</span>
          <p>Open your browser's <strong class="text-white">DevTools → Network tab</strong> while using any tool. You'll see zero requests to external servers.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-terminal-green shrink-0">2.</span>
          <p>Inspect the <a href="https://github.com/vespillo-tech/privacyterminal" class="text-terminal-cyan">source code</a>. Every tool's logic is in plain JavaScript — no obfuscation, no minification of tool logic.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-terminal-green shrink-0">3.</span>
          <p>Check our <strong class="text-white">Content Security Policy</strong> headers — they block external scripts and connections by default.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-terminal-green shrink-0">4.</span>
          <p>Use browser extensions like <strong class="text-white">uBlock Origin</strong> or <strong class="text-white">NoScript</strong> to verify no hidden requests occur.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Tech stack -->
    <section class="border-t border-terminal-border pt-6">
      <h2 class="text-terminal-amber text-glow-amber text-xs uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">
        > Tech Stack
      </h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 gap-3 text-xs">
        <div class="text-terminal-muted"><span class="text-terminal-green">framework:</span> Astro</div>
        <div class="text-terminal-muted"><span class="text-terminal-green">styling:</span> Tailwind CSS</div>
        <div class="text-terminal-muted"><span class="text-terminal-green">hosting:</span> Cloudflare Pages</div>
        <div class="text-terminal-muted"><span class="text-terminal-green">fonts:</span> JetBrains Mono (self-hosted)</div>
        <div class="text-terminal-muted"><span class="text-terminal-green">crypto:</span> Web Crypto API</div>
        <div class="text-terminal-muted"><span class="text-terminal-green">tools:</span> Client-side JS</div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
